Nelly Furtado tells @billboard that she was inspired by Madonna’s ‘Ray Of Light’ and Janet Jackson’s ‘Janet’ when making ‘Loose’:

“I felt like those were iconic pop albums where those grown women making pop music but having it be special and unique in some way, and just, like, kinda streamlined. I knew I wanted something more streamlined than my other albums.”
